The paper deals with visual recognition tasks using deep learning approaches and focuses on handling label noise in image datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model that introduces a quality variable to represent the trustworthiness of noisy labels, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the mismatch between latent and noisy labels, which involves natural language processing techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of SGD algorithm and reparameterization tricks, which are optimization techniques, falling under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with image datasets, which is a multimedia sub-category, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
